posts.cooked:
Interesting issue I am having here, never seen this before. Every single time I try to deploy code to the roborio, it does successfully and then returns this:

Now I used FTP to look at the robotio, to see if I could copy one I found on my pc, but the file does exist on the robotio. Im confused

posts.name: Tyler Veness
posts.cooked: It’s not saying libCTRE_PhoenixCCI.so couldn’t be found. It’s saying libFRC_NetworkCommunication.so.22, a library libCTRE_PhoenixCCI.so links to, couldn’t be found. Did you use a 2022 version of CTRE’s vendordep in a 2023 robot project by mistake?
potentially, how can I fix this, I think ive reinstalled the right json

posts.name: Tyler Veness
posts.cooked: Once you’ve put the proper json in the vendordeps folder, just run a build/deploy.
No, ive looked at the vendordeps and it says that I have the 2023 version. frcYear is set to 2023

posts.name: Tyler Veness
posts.cooked: If that’s the case, it makes no sense that it would be linked to the 2022 version of netcomm.

posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked:
Have you run a build when connected to the internet?

What is the exact version in the file, not just the frcYear?

Yeah I have run the build when connected to both WiFi and ethernet. Currently on version: 5.31.0+23.2.2 JSON URL: https://maven.ctr-electronics.com/release/com/ctre/phoenix/Phoenix5-frc2023-latest.json

posts.name: Ryan Blue
posts.cooked: Is there another phoenix vendordep json in the vendordeps directory?
Sorry, went to sleep and didn’t see this. Not, I only have Phoenix is there
